    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Key takeaways'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='96429' id='3' type-v2='text' w='69538' x='13231' y='2857'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>1. Bedtime Routines and Screen Time (Urban vs Rural)</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Urban residents generally have more structured, work-oriented routines, while rural residents follow more traditional, physically active daily patterns. However, rural residents report slightly higher screen time before bedtime compared to urban residents, reflecting increasing access to digital devices in rural areas.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>2. Screen Time vs Sleep Quality</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Higher screen time before sleep is associated with lower sleep quality and reduced daytime energy in both urban and rural groups. The relationship is statistically significant, with a stronger negative effect observed among rural residents, indicating screen use has a greater impact on their sleep.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>3. Work Hours vs Sleep Quality and Energy</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Work hours have little to no significant impact on sleep quality and energy among urban residents, while rural residents show a small but statistically significant negative relationship. Overall, the effect of work hours is weak, but slightly more noticeable in rural areas.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>4. Habits That Improve Sleep and Energy</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Reducing screen use before bedtime, maintaining a consistent sleep schedule, creating a stress-free environment, and engaging in relaxing activities are the key habits associated with better sleep quality and higher daytime energy.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
