                      </worksheet>
                      <dashboard name='Improvement'>
                        <zone id='39'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The chart shows that the most common habit believed to improve sleep quality is reducing screen use (20.69%), suggesting that many people think using phones less before bedtime helps them rest better. This is followed by having a stress-free environment (18.14%) and maintaining a consistent sleep time (16.92%), indicating the importance of a calm setting and routine. Relaxing activities (15.09%) are also commonly practiced. In comparison, fewer people selected habits such as exercising regularly (10.50%), avoiding caffeine late (9.68%), and using alarms or reminders (8.97%).</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Overall, habits related to reducing stimulation and maintaining routine appear to be more commonly valued for better sleep.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>From these, taking first four most common habit believed to improve sleep quality</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
