                                  <field>[federated.052b2qe1aire4u15i32y411tifre].[none:Calculation_1344475699896322:nk]</field>
                                  <field>[federated.052b2qe1aire4u15i32y411tifre].[sum:Pivot Field Values:qk]</field>
                                  <field>[federated.052b2qe1aire4u15i32y411tifre].[pcto:sum:Pivot Field Values:qk]</field>
                                </columns>
                              </tuple-descriptor>
                              <tuple>
                                <value>&quot;Sms Reminders&quot;</value>
                                <value>68</value>
                                <value>0.06889564336372847</value>
                              </tuple>
                            </tuple-reference>
                          </tuple-selection>
                        </selection-collection>
                      </worksheet>
                      <dashboard name='Habits &amp; Support (2)'>
                        <zone id='41'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The chart shows that the most preferred feature in a sleep support mobile app is reminders to reduce screen use (21.68%), indicating that users value help in limiting phone usage before bedtime. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Other popular features include sleep tracking statistics (15.40%), tips for better bedtime (14.59%), and tools to help manage schedules (14.18%), suggesting that users are interested in both guidance and monitoring of their sleep habits. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Features like education (14.08%) and relaxation or breathing exercises (13.17%) are also moderately preferred. SMS reminders (6.89%) are the least preferred, showing lower interest in this type of notification.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>From these, taking first four most preferred features. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Key Takeaways from the Study' captured-sheet='Key takeaways' id='27'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='Key takeaways'>
                        <zone id='3'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>1. Bedtime Routines and Screen Time (Urban vs Rural)</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Urban residents generally have more structured, work-oriented routines, while rural residents follow more traditional, physically active daily patterns. However, rural residents report slightly higher screen time before bedtime compared to urban residents, reflecting increasing access to digital devices in rural areas.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>2. Screen Time vs Sleep Quality</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Higher screen time before sleep is associated with lower sleep quality and reduced daytime energy in both urban and rural groups. The relationship is statistically significant, with a stronger negative effect observed among rural residents, indicating screen use has a greater impact on their sleep.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>3. Work Hours vs Sleep Quality and Energy</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Work hours have little to no significant impact on sleep quality and energy among urban residents, while rural residents show a small but statistically significant negative relationship. Overall, the effect of work hours is weak, but slightly more noticeable in rural areas.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>4. Habits That Improve Sleep and Energy</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Reducing screen use before bedtime, maintaining a consistent sleep schedule, creating a stress-free environment, and engaging in relaxing activities are the key habits associated with better sleep quality and higher daytime energy.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Recommendations for Improving Sleep Health' captured-sheet='Recommendation' id='28'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='Recommendation'>
                        <zone id='3'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>1. Reduce screen use before bedtime</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Limit screens 30–60 minutes before sleep to improve sleep quality.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>2. Keep a consistent sleep schedule</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Go to bed and wake up at the same time every day to support better rest and energy.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>3. Focus on applying good habits</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Move from knowing healthy sleep practices to actually practicing them daily with reminders and routines.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>4. Use sleep-support apps</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Apps with features like screen-time reminders, sleep tracking, and bedtime alerts can help build better habits.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>5. Adjust strategies for different groups</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Urban people may need stress and work-life balance support, while rural people may need help reducing nighttime screen use.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>6. Prioritize sleep as essential</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Treat sleep as a key part of health and productivity, not something optional.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>7. Include interactive website self-assessment</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Provide an online self-assessment tool where users can evaluate their sleep habits and receive personalized feedback and recommendations.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Conclusion' captured-sheet='Conclusion' id='29' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='63382' id='6' story-point-id='31' type-v2='text' w='72835' x='6004' y='22095'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>As part of my internship, I conducted an online survey to better understand lifestyle habits, sleep routines, screen use, and work patterns among urban and rural residents in Bhutan. The objective of the study was to analyse how daily lifestyle patterns particularly bedtime routines, screen time, and work habits affect sleep quality and daytime energy levels. A total of 366 respondents participated, providing valuable insights into these everyday behaviors.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The findings are structured across several key areas:</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Respondent distribution</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>, providing context to the sample. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Core insights</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>, including differences in average working hours, average screen use before bed, and average sleep hours between urban and rural populations. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Correlation insights</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>, examining how average working hours, screen use, and sleep duration relate to sleep quality and daytime energy levels. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Habits that influence sleep quality.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Preferred features for sleep support applications.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Future interest in using such tools.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Key takeaways from the study.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Practical recommendations for improving sleep health.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Overall conclusion</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>, tying together how lifestyle patterns shape sleep and well-being. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{9B2190AB-4D2B-488C-A482-4CEBBCBCF4DA}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='core'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
